South African doctor: Omicron has strong transmission, but mostly mild symptoms
Many doctors and medical experts in South Africa believe that the Omicron variant of the coronavirus causes milder symptoms than the delta variant, although it spreads faster.
According to the Associated Press, as the Ormicron variant spreads in South Africa, a physician group of more than 5,000 doctors in Gauteng province, South Africa, reported that the symptoms they are currently treating are mild, such as body aches and coughs, and other flu-like symptoms.
Dr Unben Pillay, the group's director, said he sees dozens of patients every day, but none have required hospitalization.
"They were able to control the disease at home, and most recovered within 10 to 14 days of isolation," Pillay said.
That includes older patients and those with medical conditions, who would otherwise be more at risk of becoming seriously ill from the coronavirus, he said.
In contrast, in the last wave of Delta, he said, the patients he treated with Covid-19 had "difficulty breathing and low blood oxygen levels.
Many will be hospitalized within a few days."
In the two weeks after the first report of the mutant Omicron strain in southern Africa, other doctors shared similar experiences.
While it will take several weeks to gather enough data, doctor observations and early evidence provide some clues.
According to the summary of the National Institute of Infectious Diseases of South Africa:of the new crown patients hospitalized in recent weeks, only 30% were severely ill, which is half of the severe disease ratio in the previous wave; the average hospital stay was shortened from 8 days to 2.8 days; only 3% of recent patients died, and in the early outbreak in South Africa, the death rate reached 20%.
"At the moment, almost all indications are that this is a milder disease," said Willem Hanekom, director of the African Health Institute, citing data from the National Institute of Infectious Diseases and other reports.
He added: "It's still early days and we need to get late data.
Typically hospitalizations and deaths come later, and we are only two weeks into this wave.”
Meanwhile, scientists around the world are watching case numbers and hospitalization rates, while testing the effectiveness of current vaccines and treatments.
While Delta remains the dominant strain of coronavirus worldwide, Omicron cases are emerging in dozens of countries, with South Africa at the epicenter of the outbreak.
Gauteng saw a 400 percent increase in new cases in the first week of December, with tests showing the Omicron variant accounted for more than 90 percent of cases, according to health officials.
Education Review: What to rely on to save abducted children?
If we compare it to the famous public service advertisement slogan "No buying, no killing," then in a favorable environment where there is no demand of "abducting abduction", mass prevention and control and all people fighting against abduction make trafficking unprofitable, risky, and cost high, and such crimes will not happen again and again.
Recently, the emergency release platform for missing children information developed by the Criminal Investigation Bureau of the Ministry of Public Security was launched.
This is an Internet information platform created to establish an authoritative channel for the release of missing children information and to retrieve abducted children in time.
I heard that the app is called "Reunion", I felt warm.
The new technology means is not only named "literary" and full of feelings, but also can be used properly, practical and effective.
The primary goal of trafficking and law enforcement is to find the abducted children and protect their personal safety and freedom.
The second is the trial and punishment of the suspect.
The meaning of criminal punishment, from individual punishment, social prevention to legal education, can be listed many "big words".
However, before the abduction case is solved, the personal safety of the victim should be given priority.
The priority of the matter, under the urgent "rescue" purpose, such as "whether abducted children should be sentenced to death" and other widely controversial裱 can be put on hold, and discussed cautiously; however, the rescue of abducted children cannot wait.
According to the investigation experience of such cases, human traffickers are accustomed to stay away from the crime site as soon as possible after they succeed.
If the kidnapping operation is delayed by one more minute, the child may be a step further away from the parents, and the difficulty of the case will increase by one point.
Under such circumstances, it is indeed a pragmatic action to come up with an effective method such as the "Reunion" platform that can directly help to detect cases and retrieve the child.
After all, "fighting abduction" is a big task that requires the operation of the entire legal system.
To combat crime and protect the rights and interests of children and parents, from the improvement of legislation, to judicial protection, and meticulous law enforcement, there is no need to implement the care of "nursing and supporting the weak".
In addition, the prevention of child trafficking, from the family to the society, can be done better.
For example, in a common case, a family of three rests at the train station, the parents are sound-sleeping, only to wake up to find that the child is missing.
A two-year-old child cannot be expected to have adequate self-protection skills, but as a parent of a young child, you should have at least a fair amount of protection.
Taking turns resting between parents, or keeping children under secure protection, is the least of the tactics to prevent child abduction.
From the other side of the police’s crackdown on abduction and trafficking, the party purchasing abducted children should also be concerned and punished.
A single wrongful act is often just one link in a long chain.
According to China's "Criminal Law", the statutory penalty for child abduction is five years; if the circumstances are particularly serious, the punishment may be the death penalty and confiscation of property.
The penalization point is high and the maximum punishment is severe. Under the general trend of "light punishment", the crime of child trafficking is obviously a crime with heavier punishment.
But there are still many cases of trafficking cases every year.
It can be seen that some people have backward concepts in raising children and weak legal awareness.
Legal education for these people should be followed up simultaneously.
To effectively control the crime of trafficking, we cannot rely solely on the official and strict law enforcement.
If the "market" for abduction exists widely, and the traffickers are full of greed, constantly innovating methods of abduction and forming a "fighting" situation with law enforcement, the addiction campaign will inevitably fall into the quagmire of inefficiency.
Therefore, breaking out of backward concepts and popularizing legal knowledge will also help to eradicate the crime of kidnapping and buying children.
