Kairou Aminus revealed that the latest batch of anti-counterfeiting paper had arrived in Kuala Lumpur on the 6th of this month, and was handed over to the printing company on the 8th for some printing.
"The bureau will send someone to pick up the goods in Kuala Lumpur next Thursday, and return to Sabah for the final phase of printing immediately. It is estimated that it will be delivered to the applicant in two more working days (December 20)."
"We will notify applicants to go to local branches to collect the birth certificate."
He added that Sabah has issued a total of 24,801 birth certificates so far this year.
