Don't scare people at the starting line - Xinhua English.news.cn
When visiting the book market, you can often feel the popularity of successful books.
Most success books today preach "best principles"-that is, assuming or implying that you can "do it" and then telling you "what" you need to do.
It is like saying that the "how to do it" is actually the most important and fundamental link.
As such, all of these books have one thing in common – either do your best at it or do nothing at all; either 100 or 0; either you go to Mount Tai, or you just stay put.
This "best principle" will admit that it is "very true", but 99% of people will be intimidated before the starting line.
Because this theory advocates a path of "you have to make up your mind, start over, and make a 180-degree change", which is precisely the fatal weakness of many people.
For those who stick to convention, conform to the old, and refuse to change, you have to yell "you want to change" in his ear, which is undoubtedly self-deception and playing the piano to the cow.
The vast majority of people will show their fear in front of the word "change", hold back and struggle to make up their minds; or on impulse, they will make a decision to "change" and take the first step bravely, but often things don't last long, they lose a competitive advantage if they persist for a while. It is hard to see continuity.
Mr. Ma Sanli's famous cross talk "Starting From Tomorrow" is a classic that most vividly expresses this "universal human nature".
The biggest problem with the "best principle" is that the threshold is too high, it often exceeds the limit of ordinary people's ability, and makes most people "stunned."
Perhaps, the "second best principle" is a way that might put more ordinary people on the path of relative success.
The core of the "second best principle" is to "lower the threshold" - which encourages a kind of "small wins for the big wins" theory, that is, if you can't achieved 100, you can only do 1: because 1 is always greater than 0; if you can't climb Mount Tai, just climb the small sand dunes in front of your house, because that is always better than standing still.
In short, as long as you do something, it is better than nothing.
Because the threshold is greatly reduced, there are more possibilities for ordinary people to persist, and as long as they persist in everything, the probability of success will also increase.
It's just that the road to success following the "second best principle" is a little longer.
All in all, although the "best principle" is supposed to make everyone succeed on the surface, it actually motivates a small number of people in the end; and the "second best principle" can effectively motivate more people and benefit as many people as possible.
The reserves of naked carp in Qinghai Lake increased by 7,100 tons this year - Xinhua English.news.cn
Xinhua News Agency, Xining, Dec. 11 (Reporters Luo Xiaofei and Zhang Hongxiang) The reporter learned from the Qinghai Provincial Department of Agriculture and Rural Affairs that the latest monitoring results show that the reserves of naked carp resources in Qinghai Lake have increased by 7,100 tons this year, reaching 108,500 tons, an accumulative increase of more than 40 times compared to the initial period of protection in 2002.
Qinghai Lake naked carp, commonly known as "huangyu", is a unique and precious fish species in Qinghai Lake, which plays a pivotal role in maintaining the safety and biodiversity of the "water-fish-bird" ecological chain in the Qinghai Lake basin.
In the 1960s and 1970s, due to a large number of human-made hunting and the degenerate environment of naked carp breeding water, the number of naked carp in Qinghai Lake decreased sharply. In 2002, the reserves of naked carp in Qinghai Lake was only 2,592 tons.
In 2004, the Qinghai Lake naked carp was listed as an endangered species in the "China Red List of Species".
Since 2003, Qinghai Province has implemented a stagnant lake for fish breeding, prohibiting any unit, collective or individual from catching naked carp in Qinghai Lake and the main rivers and tributaries in the lake area, and prohibiting the sale of naked carp and its products.
At the same time, through measures such as artificial proliferation and release, cleaning of the main rivers and rivers of Qinghai Lake, and scientific and reasonable design of "fish passages", continuous efforts in protection are continued. The reserves of naked carp resources in Qinghai Lake are increasing year by year.
Yang Lin, deputy director of the Qinghai Provincial Department of Agriculture and Rural Affairs, introduced that up to now, nearly 180 million barley carps have been artificially propagated and released in Qinghai Lake, contributing more than 23% to the restoration of Qinghai Lake naked carp resources.
The Three Rivers source region of Qinghai is an important ecological barrier and water conservation area in China and even in Asia, while Qinghai Lake is a natural barrier and ecological function area controlling the eastward spreading of desertification in the west.
In order to protect the ecological environment of the Three Rivers Headwaters and Qinghai Lake, protect aquatic wildlife, and maintain the biodiversity of the Qinghai-Tibet Plateau, Qinghai has issued prohibitions on fishing in key waters of the Yangtze River, Yellow River, and Qinghai Lake since the beginning of this year, and constructed a comprehensive management system for a management system of "one river, one river and one lake".
